OL,3,CWhy are you still paying for a
OL,4,Clandline you do not need?
OL,6,FBroadband customers in Jersey are
OL,7,Fcalling for greater transparency over
OL,8,Fcharges for landlines they do not need.
OL,10,FThe island's competition regulator
OL,11,Fsays the fees could be scrapped as a
OL,12,Fconsultation is underway to shape the
OL,13,Ffuture of the telecoms industry.
OL,15,FOne of its proposals is for a
OL,16,Fbroadband-only service, as customers
OL,17,Fcurrently have to pay for a landline
OL,18,Fand broadband to access the Internet.
