OL,3,CWhy are you still paying for a
OL,4,Clandline you do not need?
OL,6,FThis is despite both services being
OL,7,Fprovided by one fibre optic cable
OL,8,Fsince the island-wide rollout.
OL,10,FBefore the move to fibre optic, a
OL,11,Flandline was required for both phone
OL,12,Fcalls and internet access on the old
OL,13,Fcopper network, but this was gradually
OL,14,Freplaced by 2018.
OL,16,FSince then, islanders have been
OL,17,Fconfused about what they are paying
OL,18,Ffor.
