OL,3,CWhy are you still paying for a
OL,4,Clandline you do not need?
OL,6,FCustomer Thomas Hunter says: "Don't
OL,7,Fneed it, don't want it, don't use it,
OL,8,Fnever going to want it. It's just
OL,9,Fwrong. Why should I pay for something
OL,10,FI don't want or never going to use?
OL,12,F"Tell me the truth, if it's the truth
OL,13,Fit's the truth. If you want to make
OL,14,Fmore money, fair enough, and if you
OL,15,Fare getting away with it, good luck to
OL,16,Fyou, but don't give me all the rubbish
OL,17,Fthat you have to have it and need it
OL,18,Fand we have to pay for the maintenance
OL,19,Fand all that."
