OL,3,CWhy are you still paying for a
OL,4,Clandline you do not need?
OL,6,FCarl Walker, Chair of Jersey's
OL,7,FConsumer Council, says the company
OL,8,Fneed to be more open, explaining:
OL,9,F"This is a regular question we are
OL,10,Falways asked at the Consumer Council
OL,11,Fbecause people don't understand why
OL,12,Fthey are being charged for a landline
OL,13,Fwhen they don't have one and haven't
OL,14,Fused one for years.
OL,16,F"If nothing else, there is a bit of
OL,17,Feducation that needs to be done to
OL,18,Fexplain to people what it is that you
OL,19,Fare paying for.
