OL,3,CWhy are you still paying for a
OL,4,Clandline you do not need?
OL,6,FJustifying the charge, Pip Carpenter,
OL,7,FHead of Commercial Markets at JT,
OL,8,Fsays: "Your telecom services are
OL,9,Fdelivered into your house through one
OL,10,Faccess point, very similar to your
OL,11,Fwater charges and your electricity
OL,12,Fcharges, there is one pipe into the
OL,13,Fhouse.
OL,15,F"Now with telecom services through
OL,16,Fthat access point, you have both your
OL,17,Flandline and your broadband services
OL,18,Fdelivered over that same access charge.
